⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Nehemia Ytger
node M1 · M1 · ⟦Nehemia Ytger:M1:b70040⟧

WHO   — Nehemia Ytger — Princess of Eyllwe
WHAT  — A central figure of Throne of Glass — a foreign royal at the heart of Adarlan, the assassin's first true friend, and a keeper of old words and quiet purposes the crown would not approve of.
WHERE — M1 · Maas  Framework inputs: Throne of Glass — book one  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because a conquered people are not a defeated one; because friendship can be the one honest thing in a court built on lies; because some are willing to carry the weight of their nation's hope, whatever it costs.
HOW   — By a brilliant mind that masters Adarlan's tongue in weeks; by royal poise and a watchful, unbending will; by knowledge of the ancient Wyrdmarks and a courage she gives to the friend who needs it.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I am the princess of Eyllwe — and I will not be afraid.

